  "texts": [
    "To mitigate the leaking of personal information from PLMs due to memorization [23], there are several general techniques.",
    "During the pre-processing phase, the process of de-duplication and training data curation [45] has the potential to significantly decrease the amount of memorized text in PLMs.",
    "Consequently, this results in a reduction of stored personal information within these models [130].",
    "Prompt-tuning can also be a potential mitigation against memorization.",
    "The basic idea is to optimize prompts in the attack environment to evaluate the capability to extract the memorized content in a target model."
  ],
